# Projocalypse stack conventions

## Package manager

- **pnpm only** for Node/TypeScript; never npm or yarn lockfiles. See **`projocalypse-pnpm.mdc`**.

## Architecture

| Layer | Stack |
|-------|--------|
| UI | React 19, TypeScript, Vite |
| Routing | react-router-dom |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v4, `src/styles/globals.css` |
| Components | Radix UI primitives in `src/components/ui/` |
| Drag and drop | @dnd-kit |
| Persistence | Dexie.js + dexie-react-hooks; database name `pm-tool` |
| IDs | `uuid` |

## No backend

- All data lives in the browser (IndexedDB). No API server, Firebase, or remote sync unless explicitly scoped.
- Export/import JSON is the backup and migration path.

## File layout

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `src/components/` | UI components by feature (`layout/`, `project/`, `task/`, `ui/`) |
| `src/context/` | React context providers |
| `src/db/` | Dexie schema, operations, seed |
| `src/hooks/` | Custom hooks |
| `src/lib/` | Utilities, export/import |
| `src/models/` | Shared TypeScript types |

## Conventions

- File and directory naming: **`projocalypse-filenames.mdc`**. TypeScript symbols: **`projocalypse-typescript.mdc`**.
- Use existing `cn()` helper from `src/lib/utils.ts` for class merging.
- Prefer Dexie operations in `src/db/operations.ts` over ad-hoc DB access in components.
- View mode preference per project: `localStorage` via `useProjectViewMode`.
- Do not add server-side dependencies without an explicit user request.
